  <file original="en-us_topic_0000002554853535.xml.sdlxliff" datatype="x-neotrans-export" source-language="en-US" target-language="nl-NL" ns:projectId="2047222835169525761" ns:taskId="2047272237208764418" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:swfId="" ns:historyWfId="" ns:fileId="2047269827522396161" ns:vendorId="1525463126898159616" ns:vendorSubtype="T">
    <body>
      <trans-unit id="1" ns:sid="2047271449251606530" ns:tid="2047271810860265473" translate="no" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="REP" ns:MatchRate="100">
        <source>Why Does the Battery Not Supply Power at Night?</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="2" ns:sid="2047271449251606531" ns:tid="2047271810860265474" translate="no" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="REP" ns:MatchRate="100">
        <source>Intelligent scheduling policy (economic optimization)</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="3" ns:sid="2047271449251606532" ns:tid="2047271810860265475" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="37">
        <source>If the <ph id="f0">&lt;ph class=&quot;- topic/ph &quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000001645659009.xml#ph122067484595&quot; id=&quot;ph1959151418587&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000001596019118#EN-US_TOPIC_0000001645659009&quot; idp:userph=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;</ph> is enabled, the system dynamically adjusts the battery behavior based on the electricity price curve and load prediction.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="4" ns:sid="2047271449251606533" ns:tid="2047271810860265476" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="39">
        <source>Nighttime is usually a low electricity price period.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="5" ns:sid="2047271449251606534" ns:tid="2047271810860265477" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="40">
        <source>During this time, the battery is preferentially charged (from the grid or PV system) instead of discharging, so that it can release electricity during high electricity price periods in the daytime to obtain higher returns.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="6" ns:sid="2047271449251606535" ns:tid="2047271810860265478" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="43">
        <source>Economic optimization (low-charging and high-discharging)</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="7" ns:sid="2047271449251606536" ns:tid="2047271810860265479" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="41">
        <source>The system implements arbitrage by charging at low electricity prices and discharging at high electricity prices.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8" ns:sid="2047271449251606537" ns:tid="2047271810860265480" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="38">
        <source>The energy charged at night is reserved for discharge during high electricity price periods the next day to maximize returns.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="9" ns:sid="2047271449251606538" ns:tid="2047271810860265481" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="33">
        <source>If the battery discharges at night, the opportunity for higher electricity prices during the day may be missed.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10" ns:sid="2047271449251606539" ns:tid="2047271810860265482" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="35">
        <source>Time period restrictions in <ph id="f0">&lt;uicontrol class=&quot;+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol &quot; id=&quot;uicontrol1891019245456&quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000207784470567.xml#438333&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000002298266790#EN-US_TOPIC_0000207784470567&quot;/&gt;</ph> mode</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11" ns:sid="2047271449251606540" ns:tid="2047271810860265483" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="45">
        <source>In <ph id="f0">&lt;uicontrol class=&quot;+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol &quot; id=&quot;uicontrol158810276493&quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000207784470567.xml#438333&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000002298266790#EN-US_TOPIC_0000207784470567&quot;/&gt;</ph> mode, you need to manually set the discharge time period (for example, during high electricity price periods).</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="12" ns:sid="2047271449251606541" ns:tid="2047271810860265484" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="43">
        <source>If the discharge window is not configured at night, the battery does not discharge by default.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="13" ns:sid="2047271449251606542" ns:tid="2047271810860265485" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="SOC back-upvoeding" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="84">
        <source>Backup power SOC policy</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match">SOC back-upvoeding</target>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14" ns:sid="2047271449251606543" ns:tid="2047271810860265486" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="41">
        <source>The system sets the backup power SOC (for example, 5% to 20%) to ensure the power supply capability in the event of a power outage.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15" ns:sid="2047271449251606544" ns:tid="2047271810860265487" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="48">
        <source>If the SOC of the battery is lower than the end-of-discharge threshold at night, the system forcibly stops discharging.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
    </body>
